    "In the former step, a function for the expectation of the log-likelihood is created and evaluated using the current parameter estimates.",
    "In the M-step, the parameters maximizing the expected log-likelihood function found in the E-step are computed to obtain improved parameter estimates.",
    "In recent years, the rise of machine learning has also affected the area of choice modelling.",
    "According to van Cranenburgh et al. (2022), machine learning advanced considerably when it comes to estimation algorithms that are able to deal with large volumes of data and complex model specifications.",
    "These algorithms can also be employed for the estimation of choice models."
